---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import CrossBridge from '../../components/CrossBridge.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Field Notes · OASTL"
  description="OASTL Field Notes — dated updates on the Oregon school-trust case, public filings, and coalition work."
  path="/field-notes/"
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Field Notes"
    title="Dated notes on the Oregon school-trust case."
    dek="Field Notes records important changes in the case record: new filings, court rulings, source documents, and public updates that help readers follow what is happening and why it matters."
  />

  <section class="bg-oastl-bone">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-16">
      <div class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-oastl-forest mb-6">
        Week of May 18, 2026
      </div>

      <article class="border border-oastl-forest/20 bg-oastl-cream/30 rounded-sm p-6 sm:p-8">
        <div class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-oastl-gold mb-3">
          May 24, 2026
        </div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-oastl-forest font-semibold leading-tight">
          Six updates to the Oregon case record.
        </h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-[16px] text-oastl-ink/85 leading-relaxed font-serif">
          <p>
            This update added six pieces of context that help readers follow the active Oregon school-trust cases:
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li>The State's May 13 Motion for Summary Judgment is now noted on the case-history page.</li>
            <li>Judge Andrew Combs's two letter opinions, dated February 26, 2024 and March 6, 2025, are identified as key rulings in <em>Siuslaw School District 97J et al. v. State of Oregon</em>, 24CV38372.</li>
            <li><em>Comcast of Oregon II v. City of Eugene</em>, 346 Or 238 (2009), is included because it helps explain why claims about lawmaking are not treated like ordinary tort claims under Oregon law.</li>
            <li>The Pendleton School District 16R connection is explained: the same district that won a 2009 school-funding enforcement case is part of the 2026 <em>Advocates</em> plaintiff group, and Siuslaw 97J plays a similar role in 24CV38372.</li>
            <li>The January 28, 2026 Court of Appeals ruling is described as Oregon catching up with other school-trust states that already allow beneficiaries to sue, rather than as a national first. The State has asked the Oregon Supreme Court to review the ruling.</li>
            <li><em>Cascadia Wildlands v. Department of State Lands</em>, 365 Or 750 (2019), is included because the State relies on it, and OASTL points readers to the limits of that argument.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </article>

      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-4">
        <CrossBridge
          building="OASTL · Legal Desk"
          href="/legal-desk/"
          prompt="The May 13 Motion for Summary Judgment, the January 2026 ruling, and the active case file"
        />
        <CrossBridge
          building="OASTL · Briefing Room"
          href="/briefing-room/"
          prompt="The Oregon record — Common School Fund, Elliott State Forest, Cascadia Wildlands, and the repair path"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
